The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's desire for companies to hire and grow in America, raise wages for American workers, and help rebuild American cities and towns. It highlights the need to reform aspects of the National Ambient Air Quality Standards (NAAQS) program, which are considered outdated, inefficient, and barriers to growth. The Trump Administration aims to provide regulatory certainty and reduce delays in the NAAQS implementation to promote economic growth. These reforms are also seen as a way to strengthen American manufacturing.